ns in which political parties have traditionally been rooted. Weaving together major themes in American political history—including globalization, the decline of organized labor, loss of locally owned industries, uneven economic development, and the emergence of grassroots populist movements—Partisans and Partners is a timely and comprehensive analysis of American politics as it happens on the ground.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aKeynesian economics. 0aPolitical partieszUnited States. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aAmerican politics.  aIowa Caucuses.  aObama campaign.  acivil society.  acommunity study.  aethnography.  aneoliberalism.  apartisan polarization.  apolitical heuristics.  apolitical parties.  aurban politics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831107109840 cprintz978022640255040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226402727423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226402727/original  a978-3-11-071098-4  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles